        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(docs): add docs_map.md for LLM navigation (fixes #69442)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw has 670+ doc pages across automation/, channels/, cli/, concepts/, gateway/, install/, nodes/, plugins/, providers/, tools/, web/, and more. LLM agents currently have to discover this tree through trial and error. A single `docs_map.md` fixes that by providing a structured outline of every page's headings.\n\nThis follows the pattern established by [code.claude.com/docs/en/claude_code_docs_map.md](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude_code_docs_map.md) — a docs map that lets an AI read one file and know exactly what concepts are inside each page.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add `scripts/generate-docs-map.mjs` — walks `docs/`, extracts front-matter title and H2/H3/H4 headings, outputs structured `docs/docs_map.md`\n- Add `pnpm docs:map` script to `package.json`\n- Generate `docs/docs_map.md` covering 671 pages with 4672 headings\n\n## How to Regenerate\n\n```bash\npnpm docs:map\n```\n\n- [x] AI-assisted (Hermes Agent)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** Adds a docs_map.md navigation file for LLM agents to discover doc pages by heading outline\n- **Environment tested:** macOS, Node.js, OpenClaw repo at commit a824df2e\n- **Steps run after the patch:** Ran `pnpm docs:map` to generate docs/docs_map.md; ran `pnpm build` to verify no build regression\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n```\n$ node -e \"const fs=require('fs'); const c=fs.readFileSync('docs/docs_map.md','utf8'); console.log('pages:', (c.match(/### /g)||[]).length); console.log('headings:', (c.match(/^- /gm)||[]).length); console.log('has_header:', c.startsWith('# Docs Map'));\"\npages: 671\nheadings: 4672\nhas_header: true\n$ grep -n 'generate-docs-map' package.json\n1574:    \"docs:map\": \"node scripts/generate-docs-map.mjs\",\n```\n- **Observed result after fix:** docs/docs_map.md is generated with 671 pages and 4672 headings; `pnpm docs:map` script is registered in package.json; `pnpm build` passes\n- **What was not tested:** CI workflow integration (auto-regeneration on docs/** push) — left as a follow-up since it requires GitHub Actions changes\n",
